bundesbank sets new repurchase tender
    frankfurt, june 2 - 
the bundesbank set a new tender for a 28-day securities repurchase
agreement, offering banks liquidity aid at a minimum bid rate of 3.50
pct, a central bank spokesman said. banks must make their bids by 1400
gmt today and funds allocated will be credited to accounts tomorrow.
banks must repurchase securities pledged on july 1. reuter 
